<h5 class="card-title">OVERVIEW</h5>
<p>This 2017 Pulse Music Video Awards is here. The Pulse Music Video Awards is an award presentation looking to celebrate the Kenyan Music Industry their songs, videos, producers, directors among others.</p>
<p>PMVA is an award presented by the Pulse Magazine to honour the best in the Music video medium. The event will be aired live on KTN HOME.</p>
<p>As part of Pulse Celebrations, The Standard Group PLC is offering the opportunity to win the following at the Pulse Music Video Awards 2017:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Video Vixen Of The Year</li>
  <li>Male Video Of The Year</li>
  <li>Female Video Of The Year</li>
  <li>New Artist Of The Year</li>
  <li>Best Collaboration Of The Year</li>
  <li>Best Choreography Of The Year</li>
  <li>Best Breakthrough Video Of The Year</li>
  <li>Best Group Video of the Year</li>
  <li>Video Producer of The Year</li>
  <li>Most Viewed Nominated Video of The Year</li>
</ul>
<p>Make sure you hashtag your music video with #PMVA2017 and tag @PulseKenya @SDEKenya</p>
<h5 class="card-title">DATES OF PARTICIPATIONS</h5>
<p><strong>29th – 17th November 2017:</strong> Call for submissions from the public</p>
<p><strong>18th – 20th November 2017:</strong> Judges Score within the given criteria</p>
<p><strong>23rd November 2016:</strong> Nominee reveal</p>
<p><strong>23rd – 6th December 2017:</strong> Final list of shortlisted nominees released & voting is opened to the public</p>
<p><strong>7th December 2017: </strong> The Awards Gala Dinner and announcement of winners.</p>
<h5 class="card-title">GENERAL</h5>
<p>By submitting a music video and participating in the awards, entrants agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. 
The Contest will consist of a Submission Period and Voting Period.</p>
<h5 class="card-title">1.SUBMISSION TERMS & CONDITIONS</h5>
<h6 class="card-title">Eligibility</h6>
<ul>
  <li>PMVA is open to any kind of music video that has been released between October 2016 – October 2017.The music videos should meet and fall under the categories provided by The Standard Group Limited.</li>
  <li>All nominees must be at least 18 years old and for those below the age of 18, a letter from the parent or guardian must be provided for participation.</li>
  <li>All nominees entering must agree to have their names, voice, and likeness used on any advertising or broadcasting material relating to this contest without any compensation or right to royalties for short use.</li>
  <li>The Standard Group Limited reserves the right to make changes to the rules and regulations of the contest as well as the final word in any disputes that should arise concerning the contest.</li>
  <li>All nominees must sign the registration form acknowledging they have read and understand the outlined terms.</li>
  <li>Nominees that must withdraw from the competition must inform The Standard Group Limited in writing at least 3 weeks prior to the Awards ceremony</li>
  <li>All the judges’ decisions are final.</li>
</ul>
<h6 class="card-title">Entries & Identification</h6>
<p>By entering the Awards, the Entrant warrants that his or her Submission and all elements thereof satisfy the content guidelines set forth above. The Entrant further warrants that their participation in and access to the Awards is strictly at the discretion of The Standard Group Limited and may be revoked at any time without cause and without notice. The Entrant agrees not to distribute or otherwise publish through the Awards any materials which: restrict or inhibit any other person from entering the Awards, or contain a virus, spyware or other harmful component or are not appropriate or pertinent to the purpose of the awards or are defamatory or offensive.  Entrants may enter as many times as they wish. Entries may only be submitted by a single Entrant.</p>

<h6 class="card-title">Publication</h6>
<p>Finalist' names and music videos will be broadcast in a special recorded broadcast to be aired on KTN HOME. The Standard Group PLC reserves the non-exclusive right to publish any entry and/or use any entry in its promotional material during or after the Awards without further compensation to the Entrants. The Standard Group PLC promotional material shall include without limitation any print or video or electronic advertising or marketing material such as posters, online images, newspaper ads, television ads, e-mails and social media content.    </p>

<h6 class="card-title">Deadline</h6>
<p>The competition opens on 20th October 2017 0000 (EAT) and closes on 17th November 2017 1800 (EAT). All music videos must be submitted no later than 2359 (EAT) 17th November 2017. The Standard Group PLC is not responsible for entries lost, late, misdirected or delayed for any reason </p>

<h6 class="card-title">Judging</h6>
<p>Scoring and Judging will be 30% judges and 70% people choice/audience voting. A panel of 5 judges will determine the scores. The judges will be local celebrities <strong>(Music Producer, A pulse rep, Showbiz rep, Industry Veteran and an auditor).</strong> Nominees will be scored by judges on a scale of 1-10 on the following criteria:-</p>
<ul>
  <li>Music Video clarity, lyrical content, and overall performance</li>
  <li>Originality of the Music video. The music video should be original and creative.</li>
  <li>The message of the song. The music should be sending a message to the audience and the message should be educative and apply to the current trends in the country.</li>
</ul>
<p>The 70% people choice/audience voting will be done online as well as through SMS voting. There will be a website where all the nominees’ music videos will be uploaded for the audience to view and vote. The highest number of votes per video will then be selected. We will partner with either Deloitte, KPMG, Viva Africa or PKF to verifying the auditing of the votes.</p>
