<h5 class="card-title">Voting Terms & Conditions</h5>
<p>Interactive audience voting will be set-up by The Standard Group Limited to enable pulse fans to vote for their favourite top 5 (five) nominees in each category in the Pulse Music Video Awards 2017. The voting has been set up to encourage public participation in the Competition.</p>
<p>After the Submission Period, 5 (five) nominees will be selected by the judges and the Voting Period will begin soon thereafter. During the Voting Period members of the public will be called upon to vote for their favourite contestant chosen from among the 5 (five) nominees in each category. This will be done through SMS sent to 22845. The fee per vote entered by the public will be Kshs 10. </p>

<h6 class="card-title">SMS Voting</h6>
<p>You may vote by sending an SMS vote for your favourite top   5 (five) nominees. You will have to text the keyword „PMVA? followed by the nominee per category number e.g. “PMVA001” to 22845. This will be done through SMS sent to 22845. The fee per vote entered will be Kshs. 5 and bundled SMS do not apply.</p>
<p>Unrecognised SMSs (SMSs where the text does not match the required voting text format or cannot be allocated to a specific Entrant) will be charged for but not counted and the subscriber who sent the SMS will not be eligible for any of the prizes.</p>
<p>Voting starts on 23rdth November 2017 at 0000 (EAT) and ends on 6th December 2017 at 1800 (EAT).  Votes made or received outside of these times will not be counted.</p>
<p>Participants are not allowed to use machines that automatically send SMS messages or automate/facilitate the answer process or any other alternative way of sending SMS messages, other than a mobile phone containing a registered SIM card. The Standard Group Limited has the right to disqualify any Participant it suspects of violating this condition.</p>
<p>The Standard Group Limited reserves the right to change these Terms and Conditions at any time, and may suspend, withdraw or re-set voting at its sole discretion. Where The Standard Group Limited does change these Terms and Conditions, this will be communicated on the The Standard Group Limited Kenya website <a href="http://www.standardmedia.co.ke">www.standardmedia.co.ke</a></p>
<p>The Standard Group Limited reserves the right to disqualify votes if it has reasonable grounds to suspect that there has been any attempt to manipulate the voting fraudulently.</p>
<p>After the SMS voting has closed, the result of the vote will be established from all votes received. Late votes, or votes not received by the time the result is calculated, will not be counted but will be charged by your service provider where applicable.</p>
